            <item row="0" column="0">
             <widget class="QLabel" name="label_103">
              <property name="text">
               <string>Auto tile for id (each screen+virtual desktop+activity has an unique id)</string>
              </property>
             </widget>
            </item>
            <item row="0" column="1">
             <widget class="QLineEdit" name="kcfg_autoTileIds">
              <property name="toolTip">
               <string>&lt;html&gt;&lt;head/&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;p&gt;Will auto tile new windows on the desktop with specified id even if &amp;quot;Auto tile newly opened windows&amp;quot; is not enabled.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Click Ctrl+Alt+A to toggle auto tiling for current window and print id to logs. Check logs by running this command in a terminal/konsole:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;journalctl -f | grep MouseTiler&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Copy the ids here. Add multiple ids by separating them by a comma.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Each screen + virtual desktop + activity have their own unique id (screen name + desktop id + activity id smashed together into a long string).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:700;&quot;&gt;Example &lt;/span&gt;(2 ids, one on screen HDMI-A-1 and one on DP-1):&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;HDMI-A-11a35dac2-5432-4011-c65f-e36d11c00345f436e08c-e9df-438e-3d74-401cb56dd6bb,DP-16c35dac2-7955-4053-a66b-e36d11c00345f436e08c-e9df-438e-3d74-401cb56dd6bb&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
              </property>
              <property name="placeholderText">
               <string>READ TOOLTIP. Comma separated - click Ctrl+Alt+A to toggle auto tiling for current window and print id to journalctl -f | grep MouseTiler</string>
              </property>
             </widget>
            </item>
           </layout>
          </item>
